The paper deals with geolocation of social media users, which involves analyzing text content and social network connections. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Among these, cs.SI and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the paper's focus on social networks and text analysis. cs.SOC and cs.IR are also relevant, as they deal with social media and information retrieval, respectively. cs.CYBER is less likely, but still possible, as the paper touches on issues of privacy and security in social media geolocation.
